<title>GERMANY: Another Bremer Vulkan yard plans spin-off.</title>
<headline>Another Bremer Vulkan yard plans spin-off.</headline>
<dateline>BREMEN, Germany 1996-09-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Schichau Seebeckwerft, a Bremerhaven shipyard, said it was splitting off from its bankrupt parent company Bremer-Vulkan-Verbund to form SSW Faehr- und Spezialschiffbau GmbH.</p>
<p>Sole shareholder will be the company's receiver, Wolfgang van Betteray. A management statement said the spin-off will mark a new beginning for the shipyard.</p>
<p>All 1,500 jobs will be maintained, and the yard has orders for ferries that will keep it busy well into next year.</p>
<p>The move follows the separation of Lloyd Werft from Bremer Vulkan, in which van Betteray is also involved.</p>
<p>-- Terence Gallagher, Bonn newsroom, 49 228 26097150</p>
